## 2. MOBILE NAVIGATION — BOTTOM TAB BAR

Desktop sidebar collapses entirely below 768px. Replace with a fixed bottom tab bar.

```tsx
// components/nav/MobileBottomNav.tsx
// Renders only on < md screens via: className="md:hidden"
// Fixed to bottom, sits above iOS home indicator

<nav
  className="
    md:hidden fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50
    bg-olive-800
    flex items-center justify-around
    border-t border-olive-700
    pb-safe  /* safe-area-inset-bottom via Tailwind plugin or manual */
  "
  aria-label="Mobile navigation"
  style={{ paddingBottom: 'env(safe-area-inset-bottom)' }}
>
  {mobileTabs.map((tab) => (
    <Link
      key={tab.href}
      href={tab.href}
      className="
        flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1
        min-w-[60px] py-3
        /* Tap target: full height ensures 44px+ */
        text-olive-400
        aria-[current=page]:text-white
        focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-gold-500
        transition-colors duration-100
      "
      aria-label={tab.label}
    >
      {/* Active: filled icon. Inactive: outline icon. */}
      <tab.icon size={22} aria-hidden="true" />
      <span className="font-sans text-caption font-medium">{tab.label}</span>
    </Link>
  ))}
</nav>
```

**Mobile tabs — 4 maximum:**
1. Dashboard (Home icon)
2. Students (Users icon)
3. Log Session (Plus icon — this is the primary action)
4. Profile (User icon)

The "Log Session" tab (index 2) uses a slightly larger icon and the `gold-500` color when active to indicate it is the primary action. Never put more than 4 tabs in the bottom bar for this application.

**Body padding for bottom nav:** All page content on mobile must have `pb-20` (80px) to clear the fixed bottom nav.

