## 3. TOUCH TARGET MINIMUMS

Every interactive element on mobile must meet these minimums. Do not compromise on this — counselors use this on school devices, sometimes while walking.

| Element | Minimum Height | Minimum Width | Implementation |
|---|---|---|---|
| Bottom nav tabs | 60px (with padding) | 60px | `min-h-[60px]` per tab |
| Primary buttons | 48px | full-width on mobile | `min-h-[48px] w-full` |
| Secondary buttons | 44px | auto | `min-h-[44px]` |
| Form inputs | 48px | full-width | `min-h-[48px] w-full` |
| List items (student cards) | 72px | full-width | `min-h-[72px]` |
| Attendance status options | 48px each | full-width option row | `min-h-[48px]` |
| Goal met/not-met toggle | 44×44px minimum | — | Use `min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px]` |
| Incident type selectors | 48px per option | full-width | `min-h-[48px] w-full` |
| Session type dropdown | 48px | full-width | Native `<select>` at `min-h-[48px]` |
| Icon-only actions (edit, delete) | 44×44px | 44×44px | `p-3` around icon ensures tap area |

