### 4.2 Textarea Behavior on Keyboard Open

When the iOS or Android keyboard opens, the textarea must remain visible. Do not use `position: fixed` for the textarea itself. The fixed submit bar is separate from the scrollable form body.

```tsx
// In the page component, detect viewport height change (keyboard open indicator)
// Apply this to the page wrapper:
<div
  className="min-h-screen flex flex-col"
  style={{ minHeight: '100dvh' }}  // dvh = dynamic viewport height — shrinks when keyboard opens
>
```

The textarea's `min-h-[160px]` gives adequate starting height. When the keyboard opens and shrinks the viewport, the user can scroll the form to reach the textarea. The fixed submit bar remains pinned above the keyboard on iOS via `position: fixed` + `bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`.

