## 5. MOBILE FORM INPUT RULES

### 5.1 Font Size — iOS Zoom Prevention

**Every form input and textarea must have a minimum `font-size: 16px` (or `text-[16px]` in Tailwind).**

iOS Safari automatically zooms the viewport when a focused input has a font size below 16px. This is jarring and breaks the layout. There is no workaround other than using 16px minimum.

```tsx
// CORRECT — 16px on all mobile inputs
<input className="text-[16px] ..." />
<textarea className="text-[16px] ..." />
<select className="text-[16px] ..." />

// WRONG — will trigger iOS zoom
<input className="text-sm ..." />   // 14px — DO NOT USE ON MOBILE INPUTS
<input className="text-xs ..." />   // 12px — DO NOT USE ON MOBILE INPUTS
```

### 5.2 Dropdowns / Select Elements on Mobile

Use native `<select>` elements on mobile. Do not use custom-styled dropdowns (Radix Select, custom popovers) for session type, session format, or grade selectors on mobile — they break on iOS Safari's WebKit rendering engine and on school district-managed Chrome on Android.

```tsx
// CORRECT — native select, full width, 16px, 48px height
<select
  className="
    w-full min-h-[48px] px-4
    bg-surface-subtle border border-olive-300 rounded
    font-sans text-body text-olive-900
    text-[16px]
    appearance-auto  /* preserve native arrow — do not remove */
    focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-olive-600 focus:border-transparent
    transition-colors duration-100
  "
>

// WRONG — custom select wrapper with hidden native element
// Do not use this pattern on mobile inputs
```

**Exception:** Custom styled dropdowns (Radix, Headless UI) are acceptable on `≥ md` breakpoints where desktop rendering is predictable.

### 5.3 Date Inputs on Mobile

Use native `<input type="date">` on mobile. Do not use a custom date picker component below `md` breakpoint.

```tsx
<input
  type="date"
  defaultValue={todayISO}
  className="
    w-full min-h-[48px] px-4
    bg-surface-subtle border border-olive-300 rounded
    font-mono text-data text-olive-900
    text-[16px]
    focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-olive-600 focus:border-transparent
  "
/>
```

### 5.4 Attendance Status — Segmented Control vs. Dropdown

On mobile, attendance status (`attended` / `no_show` / `rescheduled` / `cancelled`) renders as a 2×2 segmented button grid (see Section 4.1), not a `<select>`. The options are large tap targets, visually clear, and require no fine motor precision.

On `≥ md`, a standard `<select>` or custom dropdown is acceptable.

### 5.5 Session Goals — Progressive Disclosure on Mobile

The goal entry section is optional and visually collapsed behind a disclosure button on mobile to keep the form short.

```tsx
// components/sessions/GoalEntrySection.tsx
const [goalsExpanded, setGoalsExpanded] = useState(false)

<div className="mb-5">
  <button
    type="button"
    onClick={() => setGoalsExpanded(!goalsExpanded)}
    className="
      w-full min-h-[48px] flex items-center justify-between
      px-4 py-3 rounded border border-olive-300
      font-sans text-body font-medium text-olive-700
      hover:bg-olive-50 active:bg-olive-100
      focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-olive-600 focus-visible:ring-offset-1
      transition-colors duration-100
    "
    aria-expanded={goalsExpanded}
  >
    <span>Add Session Goals (optional)</span>
    <ChevronDown
      size={16}
      className={`text-olive-500 transition-transform duration-150 ${goalsExpanded ? 'rotate-180' : ''}`}
      aria-hidden="true"
    />
  </button>

  {goalsExpanded && (
    <div className="mt-3 space-y-3">
      {goals.map((goal, index) => (
        <GoalRow key={index} goal={goal} index={index} />
      ))}
      <button
        type="button"
        onClick={addGoal}
        className="
          w-full min-h-[44px] rounded border border-dashed border-olive-300
          font-sans text-body-sm text-olive-500
          hover:border-olive-400 hover:text-olive-600
          transition-colors duration-100
        "
      >
        + Add Goal
      </button>
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

Each goal row has:
- Text input for the goal description: `text-[16px]`, `min-h-[44px]`
- Met / Not Met toggle: two buttons, each `min-h-[44px]`, full width split 50/50

