## 7. CHARTS ON MOBILE

Charts on mobile are **view-only**. No interactive toggles, no period selectors, no drill-down. The counselor can see the chart; all interactions happen on desktop.

```tsx
// Chart container on mobile
<div className="px-4">
  <ChartCard title="Incident Frequency — Last 6 Months">
    {/* Height reduced for mobile viewport */}
    <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={220}>
      {/* Same Recharts component as desktop — ResponsiveContainer handles the rest */}
    </ResponsiveContainer>
  </ChartCard>
</div>
```

**Chart rules on mobile:**
- Height: `220px` (not 240px — preserves scroll space)
- Width: `100%` always — never fixed pixel width
- Legends: moved above the chart (`<Legend verticalAlign="top" />`) on mobile — never overlap the bars
- Y-axis labels: suppress below 400px viewport width (`tick={false}` on YAxis below sm)
- Tooltip: enabled on mobile (touch-activated)
- Period toggles (week/month/year): hidden on mobile — show only the default monthly view
- The `ResponsiveContainer` handles all of this correctly when width is `100%`

