## 8. iOS SAFARI & ANDROID CHROME GOTCHAS

### 8.1 Safe Area Insets (iPhone Notch / Dynamic Island / Home Bar)

Always account for iOS safe area insets on fixed bottom elements.

```tsx
// Fixed bottom elements — session submit bar, bottom nav
style={{ paddingBottom: 'env(safe-area-inset-bottom)' }}

// OR with Tailwind (requires plugin or manual config):
className="pb-safe"

// Never use a fixed bottom padding that doesn't account for this.
// On iPhone 14 Pro, the home indicator requires ~34px of clearance.
```

### 8.2 iOS Bounce Scroll

The entire page should not bounce-scroll on iOS. Apply `overscroll-behavior-none` to the body, but allow scroll inside the main content container.

```tsx
// In globals.css or root layout:
// body { overscroll-behavior: none; }
// Main scroll container: overscroll-contain
```

### 8.3 iOS Input Zoom — Restatement

Minimum 16px on ALL inputs. This is non-negotiable and appears in this file because it is the most common iOS regression introduced during development. If an engineer reduces a textarea font size below 16px for aesthetic reasons, it must be rejected.

### 8.4 Android Chrome: Select Element

Android Chrome renders `<select>` elements with the native Material Design picker by default. This is acceptable — do not override it with a custom component on mobile. The native picker is familiar to Android users.

### 8.5 Active State on iOS

iOS Safari does not fire `:hover` events on touch. To get visual feedback on tap, always use an `active:` Tailwind class (which maps to `:active` pseudo-class):

```tsx
// Required on all tappable elements on mobile
className="... active:bg-olive-100 active:scale-[0.99]"
```

Without `active:` states, buttons appear unresponsive on iOS. This is especially jarring for the session log submit button.

### 8.6 100vh on Mobile Browsers

Chrome on Android and Safari on iOS include the browser UI chrome in `100vh`, causing content to be cut off. Use `100dvh` (dynamic viewport height) for full-height containers.

```tsx
// WRONG
<div className="min-h-screen">   // 100vh — clips on mobile browsers

// CORRECT
<div style={{ minHeight: '100dvh' }}>   // shrinks when keyboard opens — correct behavior
// OR in tailwind.config: extend screens with 'dvh' variant
```

### 8.7 Position: Fixed + Keyboard Open (iOS)

On iOS, when the soft keyboard opens, `position: fixed` elements can jump to unexpected positions or disappear. This affects the session submit bar.

Mitigation: wrap the fixed submit bar in a container with `z-index: 40`, and ensure the form content has `padding-bottom` large enough that the last input is always scrollable above the keyboard height.

```tsx
// Rule: The session summary textarea must have at least 280px of padding-bottom
// beneath it (the combined height of the keyboard + submit bar).
// In the form wrapper:
<div className="... pb-[280px] md:pb-6">
```

