## 11. ACCESSIBILITY ON MOBILE

- All tap targets meet 44×44px minimum — specified in Section 3
- Focus rings are visible: `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-olive-600` — never suppress focus rings
- All form inputs have visible `<label>` elements above them — never placeholder-only
- All radio/checkbox inputs have visible labels that are also part of the tap target
- Escalation banner uses `role="alert"` and `aria-live="assertive"` — screen readers announce it immediately
- Bottom nav uses `aria-label="Mobile navigation"` and `aria-label` on each tab link
- The session submit button has `aria-busy="true"` during submission
- Color is never the sole differentiator — attendance segmented control uses text labels, not just color fills
